rbnSysResourcesMib.name: rbnSysResourcesMib

revisions.description: Add rbnChassisAlarmId, rbnChassisAlarmType, rbnChassisAlarmDateAndTime, rbnChassisAlarmDescription, rbnChassisAlarmProbableCause, rbnChassisAlarmSeverity rbnChassisAlarm, rbnChassisEventObjectGroup, rbnSRMIBCompliance6.
Add new rbnSRMIBCompliance, new groups rbnSseDiskGroup and rbnSseDiskEventObjectGroup, new notification group rbnSseDiskNotifyGroup.
Add rbnSRMIBCompliance4, new group rbnSRPowerExceeded, new notification group rbnSRPowerNotifyGroup, and new group rbnSRPowerExceededGroup.

Add rbnSRStorageSlot, rbnSRStorageMountTime, rbnSRStorageStatus and rbnSRStorageErrors to rbnSRStorageTable. Add rbnSRStorageFailedEvent to report device failures. Add rbnSRMIBCompliance3, rbnSRStorageGroup2 and rbnSRNotificationGroup2. Add new group rbnSRSystem. Add new objects rbnSRSystemUptime and rbnSRSystemDate.
Add notification rbnSRSwitchoverEvent, rbnSRMIBCompliance2 and rbnSRNotificationGroup.

rbnSysResourcesMib.contactinfo: Ericsson AB. Postal: 100 Headquarters Dr San Jose, CA 95134 USA Phone: +1 408 750 5000 Fax: +1 408 750 5599
rbnSysResourcesMib.description: The management information definitions for the system resources management of a network device. This MIB is viewable under all contexts.

rbnSRProcessNotifyLastUpdate.name: rbnSRProcessNotifyLastUpdate
rbnSRProcessNotifyLastUpdate.description: The value of sysUpTime when an entry in the rbnSRProcessNotifyTable was last added. Because this table is likely to contain many entries, polling of this object allows a management station to determine when re-downloading of the table might be useful.

rbnSRProcessEventNotifyEnable.name: rbnSRProcessEventNotifyEnable
rbnSRProcessEventNotifyEnable.description: Indicates whether rbnSRProcessEvent notification should be generated for this system.

rbnSRProcessNotifyTable.name: rbnSRProcessNotifyTable
rbnSRProcessNotifyTable.description: A list of process event notifications since the agent was last re-initialized. If no process event has ever been generated, this table is empty, i.e., has zero entries.

rbnSRProcessNotifyEntry.name: rbnSRProcessNotifyEntry
rbnSRProcessNotifyEntry.description: Information about a death/birth process event notification which was last generated on the particular process.

rbnSRProcessNotifyProcName.name: rbnSRProcessNotifyProcName
rbnSRProcessNotifyProcName.description: A human readable name identifying a particular process in the system.

rbnSRProcessNotifyPID.name: rbnSRProcessNotifyPID
rbnSRProcessNotifyPID.description: A decimal number uniquely identifies the process. The value 0 indicates the process has not been started.

rbnSRProcessNotifyEventCause.name: rbnSRProcessNotifyEventCause
rbnSRProcessNotifyEventCause.description: This identifies the cause of a process death/birth event. The value firstStart(1) indicates the process has been started the first time. The other values identifies the process exit status recorded on the last process death event. On the SmartEdge platform, these values correspond 1-to-1 with the values displayed by the 'show process crash-info' CLI command.

rbnSRProcessNotifyEventType.name: rbnSRProcessNotifyEventType
rbnSRProcessNotifyEventType.description: The type of event notification sent on the process described by this row of the table. The process event type death(1) indicates that the agent has been informed that the process is not available for any use. The event type birth(2) indicates that the agent has been informed that the process has been started.

rbnSRProcessNumOfSpawn.name: rbnSRProcessNumOfSpawn
rbnSRProcessNumOfSpawn.description: The number of times the process has been spawned since the system was last initialized. Note that this is different from the restart of the network management portion of the system.

rbnSRProcessNotifyLastTimeSent.name: rbnSRProcessNotifyLastTimeSent
rbnSRProcessNotifyLastTimeSent.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time this notification was last generated on the process.

rbnSRStorageTable.name: rbnSRStorageTable
rbnSRStorageTable.description: The (conceptual) table of long-term storage devices contained by the system. In particular, disk devices accessed remotely over a network are not included here.

rbnSRStorageEntry.name: rbnSRStorageEntry
rbnSRStorageEntry.description: A (conceptual) entry for one long-term storage device contained by the system.

rbnSRStorageIndex.name: rbnSRStorageIndex
rbnSRStorageIndex.description: A unique value for each long-term storage device contained by the system. The value for each physical storage device must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the agent to the next re-initialization.

rbnSRStorageDescr.name: rbnSRStorageDescr
rbnSRStorageDescr.description: A textual description of this storage device, optionally including the device's manufacturer, revision, and its serial number.

rbnSRStorageMedia.name: rbnSRStorageMedia
rbnSRStorageMedia.description: An indication of the type of media used in this long-term storage device.

rbnSRStorageRemovable.name: rbnSRStorageRemovable
rbnSRStorageRemovable.description: Denotes whether or not the storage media may be removed from the drive/slot.

rbnSRStorageSize.name: rbnSRStorageSize
rbnSRStorageSize.description: The total size for this long-term storage device. If the media is removable and is currently removed, this value should be zero.

rbnSRStorageUtilization.name: rbnSRStorageUtilization
rbnSRStorageUtilization.description: This object is the percent utilization of the storage space on a scale of 0 to 100 percent. The formula used to calculate the Utilization is as follows. used blocks * 100 Utilization = --------------------------------------------- free blocks avail to the user + used blocks Note that the divisor is the total number of blocks available to the user which is a subset of the total storage size on the device in rbnSRStorageSize.

rbnSRStorageSlot.name: rbnSRStorageSlot
rbnSRStorageSlot.description: The chassis slot number in which the controller card containing this storage device is present.

rbnSRStorageMountTime.name: rbnSRStorageMountTime
rbnSRStorageMountTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when this storage device was last mounted.

rbnSRStorageStatus.name: rbnSRStorageStatus
rbnSRStorageStatus.description: The functional status of this storage device.

rbnSRStorageErrors.name: rbnSRStorageErrors
rbnSRStorageErrors.description: The cumulative count of soft errors on this storage device.

rbnSseDiskStorageTable.name: rbnSseDiskStorageTable
rbnSseDiskStorageTable.description: File Server System Blade is a card on the SmartEdge platform that manages data on hard disks connected to the card. This table provides details of these disks.

rbnSseDiskStorageEntry.name: rbnSseDiskStorageEntry
rbnSseDiskStorageEntry.description: A entry for the disk on the SSE.

rbnSseDiskSlot.name: rbnSseDiskSlot
rbnSseDiskSlot.description: The chassis slot number in which the disk resides.

rbnSseDiskNum.name: rbnSseDiskNum
rbnSseDiskNum.description: The disk number used to identity the disk.

rbnSseDiskSize.name: rbnSseDiskSize
rbnSseDiskSize.description: Total size of the disk in GBytes.

rbnSseDiskUsed.name: rbnSseDiskUsed
rbnSseDiskUsed.description: Total disk space utilized in GBytes.

rbnSRSystemUptime.name: rbnSRSystemUptime
rbnSRSystemUptime.description: The amount of time since this system was last initialized. Note that this is different from sysUpTime in the SNMPv2-MIB [RFC1907] because sysUpTime is the uptime of the network management portion of the system.

rbnSRSystemDate.name: rbnSRSystemDate
rbnSRSystemDate.description: The host's notion of the local date and time of day.

rbnSRPowerExceededStatus.name: rbnSRPowerExceededStatus
rbnSRPowerExceededStatus.description: The status of alarm when a controller card is inserted and results in more power being drawn than recommended. If an instance of this object has the value normal, then the chassis power has not exceeded. If an instance of this object has the value failed, then it means the chassis power was exceeded on inserting a controller card.

rbnSRProcessEvent.name: rbnSRProcessEvent
rbnSRProcessEvent.description: This notification is sent each time the agent is informed of a process death/birth event.

rbnSRSwitchoverEvent.name: rbnSRSwitchoverEvent
rbnSRSwitchoverEvent.description: This notification identifies when a switchover occurs from one main processor module to a backup.

rbnSRStorageFailedEvent.name: rbnSRStorageFailedEvent
rbnSRStorageFailedEvent.description: This notification is sent when the value of rbnSRStorageStatus for a device changes to 'failed'.

rbnSRPowerExceededEvent.name: rbnSRPowerExceededEvent
rbnSRPowerExceededEvent.description: This notification identifies when a controller card is inserted and results in more power being drawn than recommended.

rbnSseDiskAlarmDateAndTime.name: rbnSseDiskAlarmDateAndTime
rbnSseDiskAlarmDateAndTime.description: The local date and time when the alarm was raised

rbnSseDiskAlarmSeverity.name: rbnSseDiskAlarmSeverity
rbnSseDiskAlarmSeverity.description: The perceived severity of the alarm.

rbnSseDiskAlarmProbableCause.name: rbnSseDiskAlarmProbableCause
rbnSseDiskAlarmProbableCause.description: The probable cause for this alarm.

rbnSseDiskAlarmDescription.name: rbnSseDiskAlarmDescription
rbnSseDiskAlarmDescription.description: A text string which conveys additional information about the alarm.

rbnIssuState.name: rbnIssuState
rbnIssuState.description: The current state of the inservice system upgrade (ISSU).

rbnSseDiskHealthDegradedAlarm.name: rbnSseDiskHealthDegradedAlarm
rbnSseDiskHealthDegradedAlarm.description: A rbnSseDiskHealthDegradedAlarm notification signifies that the hard disk health has degraded.

rbnSseDiskFailedAlarm.name: rbnSseDiskFailedAlarm
rbnSseDiskFailedAlarm.description: A rbnSseDiskFailedAlarm notification signifies that the hard disk has failed.

rbnSseDiskMissingAlarm.name: rbnSseDiskMissingAlarm
rbnSseDiskMissingAlarm.description: A rbnSseDiskMissingAlarm notification signifies that the hard disk is missing.

rbnSseDiskUnsupportedAlarm.name: rbnSseDiskUnsupportedAlarm
rbnSseDiskUnsupportedAlarm.description: A rbnSseDiskUnsupportedAlarm notification signifies that the hard disk is not supported.

rbnSseDiskOOSAlarm.name: rbnSseDiskOOSAlarm
rbnSseDiskOOSAlarm.description: A rbnSseDiskOOSAlarm notification signifies that the hard disk is out of service.

rbnSseDiskVoltageFailureAlarm.name: rbnSseDiskVoltageFailureAlarm
rbnSseDiskVoltageFailureAlarm.description: A rbnSseDiskVoltageFailureAlarm notification signifies that the hard disk voltage has failed.

rbnSseDiskOverHeatAlarm.name: rbnSseDiskOverHeatAlarm
rbnSseDiskOverHeatAlarm.description: A rbnSseDiskOverHeatAlarm notification signifies that the hard disk overheating.

rbnSseDiskReadFailureAlarm.name: rbnSseDiskReadFailureAlarm
rbnSseDiskReadFailureAlarm.description: A rbnSseDiskReadFailureAlarm notification signifies that the hard disk read failure.

rbnIssuStateChange.name: rbnIssuStateChange
rbnIssuStateChange.description: A notification reporting a change in ISSU state. The new state is returned in the notification.

rbnChassisAlarmDateAndTime.name: rbnChassisAlarmDateAndTime
rbnChassisAlarmDateAndTime.description: The local date and time when the chassis alarm was raised

rbnChassisAlarmDescription.name: rbnChassisAlarmDescription
rbnChassisAlarmDescription.description: A text string which conveys additional information about the chassis alarm.

rbnChassisAlarmProbableCause.name: rbnChassisAlarmProbableCause
rbnChassisAlarmProbableCause.description: The probable cause for the chassis alarm.

rbnChassisAlarmSeverity.name: rbnChassisAlarmSeverity
rbnChassisAlarmSeverity.description: The perceived severity of the chassis alarm.

rbnChassisAlarm.name: rbnChassisAlarm
rbnChassisAlarm.description: A rbnChassisAlarm notification signifies that an alarm has been raised/cleared on the chassis.

rbnSRMIBCompliance6.name: rbnSRMIBCompliance6
rbnSRMIBCompliance6.description: The requirements for conformance to the System Resources MIB.

rbnSRMIBCompliance.name: rbnSRMIBCompliance
rbnSRMIBCompliance.description: The requirements for conformance to the System Resources MIB.

rbnSRProcessNotifyGroup.name: rbnSRProcessNotifyGroup
rbnSRProcessNotifyGroup.description: A collection of objects providing for remote monitoring of the system process event notification.

rbnSRNotificationGroup2.name: rbnSRNotificationGroup2
rbnSRNotificationGroup2.description: A collection of notifications that may be implemented for managing the system resources.

rbnSRSystemGroup.name: rbnSRSystemGroup
rbnSRSystemGroup.description: A collection of objects providing for remote monitoring of the system information.

rbnSRPowerNotifyGroup.name: rbnSRPowerNotifyGroup
rbnSRPowerNotifyGroup.description: A notification that may be implemented for tracking power capacity exceeding limit.

rbnSRPowerExceededGroup.name: rbnSRPowerExceededGroup
rbnSRPowerExceededGroup.description: A group providing for status of the power capacity exceeding limit.

rbnSseDiskGroup.name: rbnSseDiskGroup
rbnSseDiskGroup.description: A group providing SSE disk details.

rbnSseDiskEventObjectGroup.name: rbnSseDiskEventObjectGroup
rbnSseDiskEventObjectGroup.description: A collection of rbnSseDisk notification objects.

rbnSseDiskNotifyGroup.name: rbnSseDiskNotifyGroup
rbnSseDiskNotifyGroup.description: Notifications that are implemented for SSE disks.

rbnIssuGroup.name: rbnIssuGroup
rbnIssuGroup.description: A collection of ISSU notification objects.

rbnIssuNotifyGroup.name: rbnIssuNotifyGroup
rbnIssuNotifyGroup.description: Notifications that are implemented for ISSU.

rbnChassisEventObjectGroup.name: rbnChassisEventObjectGroup
rbnChassisEventObjectGroup.description: A collection of rbnChassis notification objects.

rbnChassisNotifyGroup.name: rbnChassisNotifyGroup
rbnChassisNotifyGroup.description: Notifications that are implemented for chassis.

rbnSRMIBCompliance1.description: The requirements for conformance to the System Resources MIB. rbnSRMIBCompliance2 replaces this compliance.

rbnSRMIBCompliance2.name: rbnSRMIBCompliance2
rbnSRMIBCompliance2.description: The requirements for conformance to the System Resources MIB. rbnSRMIBCompliance3 replaces this compliance.

rbnSRMIBCompliance3.name: rbnSRMIBCompliance3
rbnSRMIBCompliance3.description: The requirements for conformance to the System Resources MIB.

rbnSRMIBCompliance4.name: rbnSRMIBCompliance4
rbnSRMIBCompliance4.description: The requirements for conformance to the System Resources MIB.

rbnSRStorageGroup.name: rbnSRStorageGroup
rbnSRStorageGroup.description: The System Resources Storage Group. Replaced by rbnSRStorageGroup2.

rbnSRProcessEventNotificationGroup.name: rbnSRProcessEventNotificationGroup
rbnSRProcessEventNotificationGroup.description: A collection of notifications that may be implemented for managing the system process. Replaced by rbnSRNotificationGroup.

rbnSRNotificationGroup.name: rbnSRNotificationGroup
